Are you looking to plan and manage global/regional IT infrastructure projects?
Look no further, we have an exciting opportunity for a Project Manager to work with a leading global bank.
Mandatory Skill-set
• Diploma/Degree in Information Technology, Computer Engineering, Computer Science or Information System;
• Has at least 5 years of working experience in managing IT Infrastructure projects;
• Strong knowledge and understanding of Agile project/program management;
• Hands on with Jira/Confluence for tracking of projects;
• Must have experience in SharePoint;
• Should have experience in financial reporting along with MS Office Applications(Word, Excel, Visio);
• Experience in project plans, milestones, measures, budgets, resource and time management;
• Ability to work efficiently under pressure and to tight deadlines;
• Must have good presentation and facilitation skills;
• Excellent communication, stakeholder management and leadership skills.
Desired Skill-set
• PMP Certified;
•... Scrum Certified.
Responsibilities
• Plan and manage large Infrastructure projects or initiatives;
• Engage in facilitating discussions with various stakeholders and confirming the requirements;
• Responsible for co-ordinating the project financials and track against the budget;
• Partner with various IT project teams to achieve project implementation on schedule and within budget;
• Manage running and monitoring of various infrastructure projects and regularly review and analyse the project scope, identify and address project risks;
• Manage project deliverables, performance goals and progress reporting across multiple projects;
• Proactively highlight issues to management to mitigate risk.
Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to [Confidential Information] at the earliest.
When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE’s website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).
Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.
EA Licence No. 07C5639

Our client is an established organization within the Banking & Financial Services domain. They are looking for a Project Manager to lead the IT application projects within the Trading and Treasury area.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Degree in Computer Science or Engineering or Information Systems;
• At least 6 years of experience with IT application project management in Banking Industry;
• Strong domain knowledge in Trading or Treasury related products;
• Knowledge in banking products e.g. Forex / Money Market , Interest Rates, Derivatives, Fixed Income, Commodities or Equities;
• Proven track record in delivering and managing the complex banking projects with experience in managing PMO;
• Experience in managing testing and quality teams;
• Proven ability to interact with various users, senior management , IT teams and external vendors effectively;
• Experience in project plans, milestones, measures, budgets, resource and time management;
• Solid organizational skills including attention to... detail and multi-tasking skill;
• Has strong leadership abilities and interpersonal skills to drive team to meet tight deadlines;
• Excellent verbal and written communication skills.

Desirable Skill(s)
• PMP Certified.

Responsibilities
• Engage in project conceptualization, defining project scope and providing business solutions based on the business requirements;
• Responsible for planning, leading, organizing, and motivating IT project teams to achieve project implementation on schedule and within budget;
• Liaise with all levels of stakeholders & vendors while providing regular project status update;
• Prepare and track project budget, project plan and activities;
• Prepare and organize Project Steering Committee meetings and Project Portfolio meetings;
• Engage senior stakeholders to discuss and address project issues and risks;
• Collaborate with Business Project Manage, business users, various technical teams and vendors;
• Drive and manage end-to-end project delivery including requirement, design, testing, deployment;
• Plan test strategy and coordinate defects review, bug fixes, re-testing and closure within project timeline;
• Perform regular quality assessment, submit quality checklist, testing and defect executive summary

:
1. Take over the project from sales and pre-sale team and perform handover session in order to internally kick-off project;
2. Participate in technical discussion and propose a technical solution to customers’ requirements;
3. Prepare necessary document in advance, including configuration scripts, label table, cable connection table, service migration plan, etc.;
4. Collect ID information from both internal team members and external partners to apply data center access in advance;
5. Site survey of the data center and export the site survey report on time;
6. Lead the planning and implementation of project onsite, including installation, racking, cabling, configuration, commission etc.;
7. Define the scope of work for new recruits and elaborate to stakeholders;
8. Manage both internal and external project resource allocation and ensure external partners performing their best;
9. Ensure that the project deliverables are on time, within budget and meet quality demand;
10. Daily... weekly, monthly and quarterly onsite report on project or customer level when it is required

Requirement:
1. Diploma/Bachelor’s degree or above in Engineering, Computer Science, Information Technology, Security or equivalent;
2. Proficient in Mandarin and English (speaking and writing);
3. Over 2 years IP or IT project delivery experience; outstanding fresh graduates are totally welcomed;
4. Basic network knowledge, such as TCP/IP protocol stacks, basic routing and switching knowledge;
5. Basic server knowledge and familiar with Linux CLI;
6. Familiar with Huawei devices (or H3C devices) and experience on network design / technical implementation is preferred;
7. Cisco CCNA, CCNP, CCIE or Huawei HCNA, HCNP, HCIE certification is preferred;
8. PMP or ITIL certification is preferred;
9. Strong ability on multitasks;
10. Able to self-management and accomplish tasks with minimal supervision;
11. Work effectively under pressure and work overtime may be required;
12. Able to travel domestic or overseas

